>I'll Sleep When I'm Dead
https://archiveofourown.org/works/39416856
(This is mostly a rant about mental health)
For extremely personal reasons I don't like this one all that much. It is a good story but as of late I have a lot experience with mental health problems between friends/lovers/myself. So my very specific hang-up with this story is it relationship progression. To go from bottom of the barrel mental health and social isolation to commited relationship isn't very healthy and he would probably be right to say he can't handle a romantic relationship right now. What he needs before she looks for romance in their relationship is a friend to help him grow a social life/some kind of support network so he has the coping mechanism for social interaction & a place to go should there be problems in the future romantic relationship. If this sort of thing doesn't happen then he would be entirely dependent on her for his mental health, happyness, and social interaction without any other options. Being in a relationship can help with a lot of mental strife but there is a bar that needs to be cleared so that even if you are not healthy you can have a healthy relationship, and anon isn't there just yet. The truth is this is something perfectly possible to ignore a lot of good stories do but it's a sore spot for me these days. As for the writing it is good I do think that there are ways to better convay mental noise than corrupted text alone it just needs a little more spice wether it's more frantic thoughts or disjointed flashbacks/flashforwards to how he has/will disappoint her/others. Sorry that my first review of your work was a sore spot for me.
